        p.
          Use these classes to set the width of block (or inline-block) elements.
          These can be very useful for items in a grid object.
        p.
          Percentage widths are fluid, best for responding to screen size.
          Pixel widths are absolute, best for when you know the exact width.
          Em widths are adjustable, based on the font size of the element
          (e.g. if the element&rsquo;s font size is 16px, then 1em is 16px
          and 5em is 80px).
